{"lemma":"لاعِبُو","slug":"لاعِبُو","root":"ل.ع.ب","root_slug":"ل-ع-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ل-ع-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"لاعِب","root":"لعب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n37794"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B9%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%8F%D9%88"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to play with (someone), to have fun with (someone), to jest with (someone)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to trifle (someone)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"player"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"athlete"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of لَعِبَ (laʕiba, “to play”)."},"ipa":["/laː.ʕa.ba/","/laː.ʕib/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n37794","headword_ar":"لَاعِبٌ","root":"lEb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Playing, sporting, gaming, jesting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"joking."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laEibN","text_ar":"لَعِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yaA^oxu*an~a","text_ar":"لَا يَاْخُذَنَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHadukumo mataAEa A^axiyhi laAEibFA jaAd~FA","text_ar":"اَحَدُكُمْ مَتَاعَ اَخِيهِ لَاعِبًا جَادًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"By no means shall any one of you take the property of his brother in play"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in earnest"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: by this is meant taking a thing without meaning to steal it, but meaning to vex and anger the owner; so that the taker is in play with respect to theft, but in earnest in annoying. (TA, from a trad.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~amaA A^anota laAEibN","text_ar":"اـِنَّمَا اَنْتَ لَاعِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou art only playing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: said to anyone who does what is unprofitable. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}